tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated HbA1c (6.2%), indicating impaired glucose metabolism or possible diabetes, despite normal fasting glucose. Erythrocyte count is slightly low, but other red cell indices and hemoglobin are normal, suggesting no significant anemia. Platelet distribution width is elevated, which may reflect increased platelet size variability but with normal platelet count. Renal and electrolyte parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for glycemic control and monitoring of hematological parameters.
